{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778982252260,"sessionID":"ses_1cc6e9e73ffe2HfOe2xPGj0ykX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_aXaqplpJmCvzHPkrEcOtUAZD","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- added a new term, `GO:7770068` `ferric iron reductase activity`, using `RHEA:71767`\n+- made `GO:0000293` `ferric-chelate reductase activity` a child of the new term\n+- corrected the `GO:0000293` definition from siderophore-specific wording to the broader chelate wording on both substrate and product sides\n+\n+One implementation note: in this local checkout, `GO:7770057` was already assigned to an unrelated term, so I used the next free local ID `GO:7770068`.\n+\n+Validation passed locally, including SPARQL checks and ELK reasoning.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+This PR addresses issue `#27593` by adding the missing general ferric iron reductase activity term and tightening the placement/definition of the existing ferric-chelate reductase term.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+\n+1. Added new term `GO:7770068` `ferric iron reductase activity`\n+- namespace: `molecular_function`\n+- definition: `Catalysis of the reaction: 2 Fe3+ + NADPH = 2 Fe2+ + H+ + NADP+.`\n+- definition provenance: `RHEA:71767`, `PMID:39940646`, `PMID:34614242`, `PMID:8321236`\n+- xrefs: `RHEA:71767 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}`, plus PMID xrefs requested in the issue\n+- parent: `GO:0016723` `oxidoreductase activity, acting on metal ions, NAD or NADP as acceptor`\n+- metadata: `term_tracker_item`, `created_by`, `creation_date`\n+\n+2. Updated `GO:0000293` `ferric-chelate reductase activity`\n+- changed the definition from siderophore-specific wording to chelate wording:\n+  `2 Fe3+-chelate + electron donor = 2 Fe2+-chelate + electron acceptor`\n+- reparented it under `GO:7770068` so the chelate-specific activity is modeled as a subclass of the more general ferric iron reductase activity\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue discussion converged on adding a general ferric iron reductase activity term corresponding to `RHEA:71767`.\n+- `GO:0000293` had a label referring to chelates but a definition narrowed to siderophores. Updating the reaction wording to `chelate` brings the definition back in line with the label and with the intended broader grouping role.\n+- I changed both the substrate and product sides of the `GO:0000293` definition to `chelate` for chemical consistency; the chelating group is not transformed by the reduction step.\n+\n+Implementation note:\n+\n+- The earlier issue thread mentioned `GO:7770057`, but in this evaluation checkout that ID is already occupied by an unrelated existing term (`copper ion import into Golgi lumen`). I therefore used the next free local ID: `GO:7770068`.\n+\n+Validation and checks performed:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context reviewed, request was clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: pre-edit SPARQL validation passed\n+- [x] RESEARCH: created local `RESEARCH.md` with validated support text for all PMIDs\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: searched existing GO terms and related reductase precedents in `go-edit.obo`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: created local `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`; no dedicated DOSDP applied, used existing molecular function reaction-term precedent\n+- [x] EDITS: used `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: parentage updated appropriately; no unnecessary logical definitions added\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: used reaction-term guidance; no CHEBI, taxon constraint, or obsoletion workflow required\n+- [x] METADATA: added required metadata only for the new term\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: post-edit SPARQL validation passed\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: ELK reasoning passed\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMIDs cached and support text validated with `linkml-reference-validator`\n+\n+Files changed:\n+\n+- `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n+\n+Local supporting files created but not committed:\n+\n+- `RESEARCH.md`\n+- `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`\n+- `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md`\n+- `PR_COMMENTS.md`\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,10 @@\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- added a new term, `GO:7770068` `ferric iron reductase activity`, using `RHEA:71767`\n+- made `GO:0000293` `ferric-chelate reductase activity` a child of the new term\n+- corrected the `GO:0000293` definition from siderophore-specific wording to the broader chelate wording on both substrate and product sides\n+\n+One implementation note: in this local checkout, `GO:7770057` was already assigned to an unrelated term, so I used the next free local ID `GO:7770068`.\n+\n+Validation passed locally, including SPARQL checks and ELK reasoning.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,52 @@\n+This PR addresses issue `#27593` by adding the missing general ferric iron reductase activity term and tightening the placement/definition of the existing ferric-chelate reductase term.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+\n+1. Added new term `GO:7770068` `ferric iron reductase activity`\n+- namespace: `molecular_function`\n+- definition: `Catalysis of the reaction: 2 Fe3+ + NADPH = 2 Fe2+ + H+ + NADP+.`\n+- definition provenance: `RHEA:71767`, `PMID:39940646`, `PMID:34614242`, `PMID:8321236`\n+- xrefs: `RHEA:71767 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}`, plus PMID xrefs requested in the issue\n+- parent: `GO:0016723` `oxidoreductase activity, acting on metal ions, NAD or NADP as acceptor`\n+- metadata: `term_tracker_item`, `created_by`, `creation_date`\n+\n+2. Updated `GO:0000293` `ferric-chelate reductase activity`\n+- changed the definition from siderophore-specific wording to chelate wording:\n+  `2 Fe3+-chelate + electron donor = 2 Fe2+-chelate + electron acceptor`\n+- reparented it under `GO:7770068` so the chelate-specific activity is modeled as a subclass of the more general ferric iron reductase activity\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue discussion converged on adding a general ferric iron reductase activity term corresponding to `RHEA:71767`.\n+- `GO:0000293` had a label referring to chelates but a definition narrowed to siderophores. Updating the reaction wording to `chelate` brings the definition back in line with the label and with the intended broader grouping role.\n+- I changed both the substrate and product sides of the `GO:0000293` definition to `chelate` for chemical consistency; the chelating group is not transformed by the reduction step.\n+\n+Implementation note:\n+\n+- The earlier issue thread mentioned `GO:7770057`, but in this evaluation checkout that ID is already occupied by an unrelated existing term (`copper ion import into Golgi lumen`). I therefore used the next free local ID: `GO:7770068`.\n+\n+Validation and checks performed:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context reviewed, request was clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: pre-edit SPARQL validation passed\n+- [x] RESEARCH: created local `RESEARCH.md` with validated support text for all PMIDs\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: searched existing GO terms and related reductase precedents in `go-edit.obo`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: created local `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`; no dedicated DOSDP applied, used existing molecular function reaction-term precedent\n+- [x] EDITS: used `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: parentage updated appropriately; no unnecessary logical definitions added\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: used reaction-term guidance; no CHEBI, taxon constraint, or obsoletion workflow required\n+- [x] METADATA: added required metadata only for the new term\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: post-edit SPARQL validation passed\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: ELK reasoning passed\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMIDs cached and support text validated with `linkml-reference-validator`\n+\n+Files changed:\n+\n+- `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n+\n+Local supporting files created but not committed:\n+\n+- `RESEARCH.md`\n+- `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`\n+- `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md`\n+- `PR_COMMENTS.md`\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,10 @@\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- added a new term, `GO:7770068` `ferric iron reductase activity`, using `RHEA:71767`\n+- made `GO:0000293` `ferric-chelate reductase activity` a child of the new term\n+- corrected the `GO:0000293` definition from siderophore-specific wording to the broader chelate wording on both substrate and product sides\n+\n+One implementation note: in this local checkout, `GO:7770057` was already assigned to an unrelated term, so I used the next free local ID `GO:7770068`.\n+\n+Validation passed locally, including SPARQL checks and ELK reasoning.\n","additions":10,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"PR_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-